@page "/privacy"
@using BecauseImClever.Client.Components

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - BecauseImClever</PageTitle>

<div class="privacy-policy">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2025</p>

    <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            At BecauseImClever, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains what data we collect,
            why we collect it, and how you can exercise your rights regarding your personal data.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>What Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>
            With your consent, we may collect the following anonymous information to help protect you from
            potentially harmful browser extensions:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Browser Fingerprint Hash:</strong> A one-way hash generated from non-identifying browser
                characteristics. This cannot be reversed to identify you personally.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Extension Detection:</strong> Information about whether certain browser extensions are
                installed that we have identified as potentially harmful.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>IP Address Hash:</strong> A hashed version of your IP address for geographic analysis.
                We never store your actual IP address.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>User Agent:</strong> Basic browser and operating system information for compatibility analysis.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Why We Collect This Data</h2>
        <p>
            We use this data to:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Warn you about potentially harmful browser extensions like Honey that may compromise your privacy</li>
            <li>Aggregate statistics to understand which harmful extensions are most common</li>
            <li>Improve our warning systems to better protect our visitors</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
            We retain extension detection data for a period of 12 months for statistical analysis purposes.
            After this period, data is automatically anonymized or deleted.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
            Under GDPR, CCPA, and similar regulations worldwide, you have the following rights:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> Request a copy of the data we have about you</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data (use the form below)</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw your tracking consent at any time</li>
            <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to processing of your data</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Consent</h2>
        <p>
            We will never collect tracking data without your explicit consent. When you first visit our site,
            you will be presented with a consent banner. You can accept or decline tracking at any time.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
            We do not share your data with any third parties. All data processing is performed by us on our own servers.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Delete Your Data</h2>
        <p>
            Use the form below to delete all tracking data associated with your browser. This action is immediate and irreversible.
        </p>
        <DataDeletionForm />
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            If you have any questions about this privacy policy or wish to exercise your rights,
            please contact us through our About page.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
